# Chocolate Swirl Pistachio Ice Cream

Based on [https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/chocolate-swirl-pistachio-ice-cream](https://sallysbakingaddiction.com/chocolate-swirl-pistachio-ice-cream)

{ rating=0 image="None" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

### Chocolate Ganache

- [ ] 6 Tbsps heavy cream
- [ ] 1/2 cup quality chocolate chips

### Pistachio Ice Cream

- [ ] 1.25 cups shelled roasted pistachios
- [ ] 2 cups heavy cream, cold
- [ ] 14-ounce can full-fat sweetened condensed milk
- [ ] 1 tsp pure vanilla extract or vanilla bean paste
- [ ] 1/4 tsp almond extract
- [ ] Optional: tiny drop green gel food coloring

### Topping

- [ ] 2 Tbsps roughly chopped pistachios
- [ ] 2 Tbsps roughly chopped chocolate chips

## Recipe

1. Heat cream until simmering, pour over chocolate chips, let sit 2-3 minutes, then stir until melted. Set aside to cool and thicken.
1. Pulse pistachios in food processor until finely ground.
1. Beat cold heavy cream on medium-high speed until stiff peaks form (about 4 minutes).
1. Add ground pistachios, condensed milk, vanilla, almond extract, and food coloring if desired. Beat on low speed until combined.
1. Spread half the ice cream mixture into a freezer-safe container, add half the ganache in spoonfuls, top with remaining ice cream, then remaining ganache. Swirl gently with a knife. Top with chopped pistachios and chocolate.
1. Cover and freeze at least 8 hours (up to 2 weeks).

## Notes

- This "no-churn method" doesn't require an ice cream maker
